b'{"data_headers":{"result_code":1},"data":{"information":{"article_id":1343,"category_name":"News","pr_category_id":"1","title_name":"Regarding the New Shared Skills Feature","message":"<div>A new feature, shared skills, was added in the version 1.20.0 update.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0What are Shared Skills?<\/div><div>Shared skills are an additional two skills that can be used by a team&#39;s leader.<\/div><div>Shared skills can be equipped by all members of the team, but only the team&#39;s leader may use them.<\/div><div>Only skills from other adventurers that meet certain conditions may be equipped.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u30fbUnlock conditions for shared skills<\/div><div>Shared skills are unlocked by clearing Chapter 2 1-1 of the main campaign on Normal difficulty.<\/div><div><img src=\\"https:\/\/dragalialost.akamaized.net\/attached\/information\/images\/c612f43b4fec47cb4b8858ecc5ce2a89.png\\"><\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Equipping and Unlocking Shared Skills<\/div><div>Shared skills can be equipped and unlocked from the Teams menu.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Once a skill has been unlocked for sharing, it can be equipped by any adventurer. Shared skills will always be the same level as the original skill.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u30fbUnlock conditions for shared skills<\/div><div>1. The adventurer whose skill you want to use must be at Lv. 80 or above and have 50 or more mana nodes unlocked.<\/div><div>2. The skill must be unlocked for sharing using elemental tomes of the same element as the skill.<\/div><div>(You can use the skills of adventurers who join during the main campaign as shared skills without unlocking them.)<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u30fbAdditional information<\/div><div>There are some skills that cannot be shared.<\/div><div>Skills that can be shared but have yet to be unlocked will be shown as &quot;Shareable (Locked).&quot;<\/div><div>Skills that do not have this text cannot be shared.<\/div><div>There are some adventurers that do not have any shareable skills.<\/div><div><img src=\\"https:\/\/dragalialost.akamaized.net\/attached\/information\/images\/6baff93578df7aa3449bbd52345142de.png\\"><\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Shared Skill Priority<\/div><div>Each adventurer has two shared skill slots, and these slots work slightly differently.<\/div><div>Shared Skill 1: When an adventurer is equipped with a weapon with a weapon skill, they will be able to equip either the weapon skill or a shared skill.<\/div><div>Shared Skill 2: When playing solo content, you can choose to use either a helper skill or this shared skill.<\/div><div>(When you are using a weapon skill in slot one and a helper skill in slot two, you will not be able to use any shared skills. When a helper skill is equipped to the Shared Skill 2 slot, you will be able to use helper skills as normal. Helper skills can be used by adventurers other than the team leader.)<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>By default, skills from adventurers that join during the main campaign will be assigned as shared skills.<\/div><div>The priority list for these automatic assignments is as follows, from highest to lowest:<\/div><div>1. Cleo<\/div><div>2. Ranzal<\/div><div>3. The Prince<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>You cannot assign skills from adventurers with the same name and epithet as support skills.<\/div><div>For example, Ranzal from the main campaign cannot use shared skills from the same version of Ranzal, but can use skills from Gala Ranzal.<\/div><div><img src=\\"https:\/\/dragalialost.akamaized.net\/attached\/information\/images\/02dbfb3c08fd445f88967994a813d545.png\\"><\/div><div>\\u25a0Skill Point Costs for Shared Skills<\/div><div>Each adventurer has a maximum number of skill points that can be used to equip shared skills, which varies for each adventurer.<\/div><div>Both shared skills&#39; combined point totals must be less than the maximum points allowed.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Even if you are playing solo using a helper skill instead of a second shared skill, the amount of points available for the first shared skill will still take into account the point cost of the user&#39;s second shared skill.<\/div><div><img src=\\"https:\/\/dragalialost.akamaized.net\/attached\/information\/images\/fb68f5eb8e58f9f3bf16370ce46b910e.png\\"><\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Unlocking Shared Skills<\/div><div>To unlock shared skills for use, you will need elemental tomes for the corresponding element.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>These can be obtained from events, or from the shop by using diamantium.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Shared Skills&#39; Efficacy<\/div><div>When a skill is used as a shared skill, the following reductions will be applied:<\/div><div>\\u30fbIts skill gauge will fill either more slowly or more quickly depending on the adventurer.<\/div><div>\\u30fbWhen a skill deals damage, its damage will be reduced.<\/div><div>\\u30fbWhen a skill restores HP, its recovery potency will be reduced.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Elemental Attunement of Shared Skills<\/div><div>\\u30fbDamage-dealing skills<br>In the event that the elemental attunement of a shared skill and the adventurer equipping said shared skill differ, the damage dealt by the shared skill will change to match the elemental attunement of the adventurer using the skill.<br>For example, if a flame-attuned adventurer uses a shared skill that would normally deal wind damage, the skill will instead deal flame damage.<br><br>\\u30fbBuff and debuff skills<br>For shared skills that provide buffs and debuffs restricted to specific elements, these buffs and debuffs will only be applied to adventurers and enemies attuned to the element specified in the relevant skill&#39;s description.<br>For example, if a flame-attuned adventurer uses a shared skill that provides a strength buff to wind-attuned adventurers, the buff will not be applied to them and will instead only be applied to any wind-attuned team members.<br><br><\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Notes:<\/div><div>\\u30fbThe information about shared skills in this notification is also available in the Adventurers section of Help under Help\/Support on the Menu at the top of the screen.<\/div><div>\\u30fbThe shared skills feature may be changed in future updates.<\/div><div>\\u30fbFor more information about elemental tomes, tap the Shop on the Home page, and see Upgrade Essentials &amp; Packs.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Thank you for playing Dragalia Lost.<\/div>","start_time":1590375600,"prev_article_id":"1327","next_article_id":"1322","image_path":"","update_time":1590390201}}}'